"Always build full-stack production-ready web applications with the following standards:
Frontend: Use React with Tailwind CSS. UI components from shadcn/ui. Icons from lucide-react. Smooth animations using Framer Motion. Fully responsive mobile first design. No lorem ipsum, always use realistic content. Beautiful modern dark theme with purple accents unless client specifies otherwise.
Backend & Database: Always use Supabase for backend, database and authentication. Design proper normalized database tables with correct relationships. Always enable Row Level Security (RLS) on every single table. Write proper RLS policies so public users can only read allowed data and cannot access admin or private data.
Security: Never hardcode API keys, emails, or passwords anywhere in the code. Always use environment variables via import.meta.env for all sensitive data. Admin email and admin password must be set via environment variables only. Admin routes must be fully protected, unauthenticated users get redirected to login immediately. All forms must have input validation and sanitization.
Admin Dashboard: Strict admin only access. Only the email and password stored in environment variables can log into the admin panel. Full CRUD operations for managing all content. Clean dashboard with stats and recent activity.
AI Receptionist: Always add a floating chat widget in the bottom right corner powered by Claude AI via Supabase edge functions. Friendly, helpful and bilingual in English and Urdu.
Code Quality: Always add proper loading states, error handling and success messages. No broken UI states. Clean commented code. All Supabase calls wrapped in try catch blocks."